snippet.title: I was in a car accident while riding in a compact car.
snippet.description: ... I was in a car accident while riding in a compact car. My knees hit the glove box and I tore the PCL of my left knee. My diagnosis is PCL insufficiency. What does this mean? The posterior cruciate ligament (PCL) is one of the major ligaments inside the knee. It helps hold the knee joint steady during motion so that the thighbone and lower leg bone move and glide without shifting. Ligaments are not very elastic. When they are torn or damaged, they don’t “spring” back. Instead, scar tissue fills in the torn area and weakness occurs. This loss of strength is called PCL insufficiency. The ligament is unable to do its job to move, hold, and protect the joint. Reference: Michael J. Strobel, MD, et al. Arthroscopic Evaluation of Articular Cartilage Lesions in Posterior Cruciate Ligament-Deficient Knees. In Arthroscopy. March 2003. Vol. 19. No. 3. Pp. 262-268.' ...

snippet.title: Frustrated with renting
snippet.description: ... I'm so frustrated with my landlord. He's good about most things, but really bad about the rent. I have been living here over 2 years and in that time have had rent paid in full no more than 2 days past the 1st of the month. Also, me being late on rent has been very rare. Due to being out of town for a couple days then being sick on top of that, I didnt get rent paid until today. Granted, I should have communicated my situation better but the landlord was not at all understanding. He wouldn't listen to anything I had to say then decided to put a $10 per day late fee if rent is ever late again. I could understand that if I was constantly late, but I'm not. I understand being a landlord is hard, but even the big rental complexes give their tenants a little leway once in a while. Thanks for "listening" to me vent. Things like this tend to get me down if I don't get it out. ...
